Rating: 3
I have to say that this was good. I ran low on red wine vinegar so we used 3tbl spoon evvo to 1 1/2tbl sp of red wine vinegar. I also only used 2 cans of beans because I only had five people eating this. I would make this again because it is good and easy to make.

Rating: 4
Really delicious, cool and filling. I used ground cumin instead of cumin seeds, adding it to the dressing to taste. I also added a touch of honey to the dressing, to balance out the very sharp red wine vinegar I had on hand. A great summer dinner.

Rating: 4
This is a great recipe that goes well with chicken or burgers. It is a healthy substitute for baked beans. I used balsamic vinegar instead of wine vinegar and added cayenne pepper and kosher salt to taste. I also used 3 kinds of beans: kidney, black, and pinto. You should only stir in the walnuts right before serving so the nuts don't get soggy. Everyone I make this for loves it! Give it a try!

